dcterms:description: A dataset generated using the Broom model, which simulates stick-slip behavior in a fault interface with bristles acting as asperities. The dataset consists of 2000 stick-slip events at various normal stress levels, capturing the dynamics of the system and the energy released during these events.
dcterms:title: Broom Model Dataset
